      "primaryGenreId": 6027,
      "isVppDeviceBasedLicensingEnabled": true,
      "releaseNotes": "More UI tweaks for older phones with smaller screens.\n// Eight new system filters\n\nFIBER DRAG (FIBR) - smears the image along a swirling flow into fibrous strands.\nDEAD SCANNER - a faulty scan head that sticks, grinds, and tears with lamp flare.\nTHERMAL SLUMP - soft midtones sag and drip like melting wax while darks stay anchored.\nREWOVEN - cuts the image into ribbons that weave, slip, and fray like cloth.\nCOLLAPSE FEEDBACK - feeds the frame into itself for interference patterns.\nDENSITY CRUSH - clusters of midtones collapse into darker masses.\nDEAD WEIGHT - drapes the image over hung silk, with darks sagging and folds shaded for depth.\nSEDIMENT - rain washes bright material down the frame in dry, granular sediment streaks.",
